benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to account

covered: Valid Request: Multiple TC scenarios (TC01-TC04, etc.) cover successful PUT with varied headers and payloads
Non-Existing Resource: TC07 verifies error when account does not exist
Authorization: TC08/TC12 cover missing headers and unauthorized access
Validation and Error Handling: Malformed JSON (TC10), invalid accountId (TC06), missing body (TC09), invalid CustomField schemas (TC11)
Large Payloads and Edge Cases: TC04 (100 fields), TC15 (empty array), TC16 (max field lengths), TC17 (extra properties) cover payload size and field validation
Security: TC20 (SQL injection) and TC21 (XSS) validate input sanitization
Concurrency: TC25 tests concurrent updates; TC22/TC19 cover retry/timeouts
Integration: TC27 (audit logs) and TC28 (external reporting system) cover integration aspects
Accessibility: TC29 verifies documentation and error message accessibility
gaps: Partial Update semantics: no explicit test to reject or allow partial updates of fields
Internal server error (500) scenario not covered
Data type validation in CustomField values beyond missing required fields not explicitly tested
Explicit test for update when server constraints fail (DB constraint) not covered
recommendations: Add test for partial update behavior and verify error if partial updates are not allowed
Add internal server error scenario (500) test
Add rate limiting tests to verify throttling
Add caching behavior tests (ETag and Cache-Control if applicable)
Add tests for data type validation within CustomField values
Add tests simulating DB constraint violations to ensure proper 5xx handling
